          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>1 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark: 2011.494; Qurʾānic Text: Q 37:113-37:118; 7 lines per page; Dimensions: 330 x 238mm; Script style: kūfī; Estimated  date  of production: 750-900.  </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The catalogue entry on the <ref target="https://hvrd.art/o/336991">museum's website</ref> contains further information, as well as the following description: </p>
              <p>"This is a folio detached from an `Abbasid-era Qur’an. It is written in  Kufic script, with seven lines to the page, in dark brown ink on  parchment.  Vocalization marks are written in red and yellow. Verse  stops are marked with gold dots or pendant-shaped marks in gold. The  text consists of Sura 37:113-mid 115 (recto); and Sura 37: mid-115-118  (verso). The verso is the flesh side of the parchment. The verses  concern Isaac; and Moses and Aaron who were given the book to guide  their people."</p>
            </summary>
